<h2>Questions We Get on These Calls</h2>

<h3>My LG dryer runs but produces no heat at all — what's most likely?</h3>
<p>On electric dryers, thermal fuse is most likely — about 60% of our no-heat calls. On gas dryers, thermal fuse first, then gas valve coils or igniter. We test all systematically from cheapest to most expensive before recommending any part.</p>

<h3>Why did my LG dryer thermal fuse blow?</h3>
<p>Almost always a clogged exhaust vent. The vent restriction causes the dryer to overheat, the fuse blows to protect against fire. Simply replacing the fuse without clearing the vent means it blows again within days. We always diagnose and fix the root cause.</p>

<h3>How do I know if my LG gas dryer igniter is bad?</h3>
<p>A working igniter glows bright white and lights the burner within 45–60 seconds. A failing igniter glows dimly orange instead of bright white, takes longer than 90 seconds, or clicks repeatedly without the burner ever lighting. Complete failure means no glow at all.</p>

<h3>Can I use my LG dryer if it's not heating?</h3>
<p>Air-dry and fluff cycles are safe. Avoid heated cycles until the repair is done — repeated failed heat attempts stress related components.</p>

<h3>Do you repair all LG dryer models?</h3>
<p>Yes — DLEX, DLGX, DLE, DLG series, all model years, gas and electric. We stock parts for the most common models. Give us your model number when you call and we'll confirm what we'll have on the truck.</p>

<h3>How fast can you come?</h3>
<p>Same day in most cases. Call (323) 990-7550 — we'll give you a 2–4 hour arrival window across Los Angeles County, Orange County, and Ventura County.</p>

